4. Personnel & Roles
	•	Chief Existential Compliance Officer (CECO):
Responsible for ensuring that participants meaningfully encounter reality.
	•	Director of Conceptual Containment:
Oversees the prevention of ideas escaping into performative rhetoric without undergoing physical instantiation.
	•	Embodiment Compliance Auditor (ECA):
Certifies that participants are using actual limbs rather than outsourced avatars.
	•	Symbolic Overproduction Mitigation Specialist (SOMS):
Monitors and reduces excessive creation of identity-adjacent symbolic outputs.
	•	Chief Irony Containment Officer (CICO):
Ensures the project does not become a performative symbol of anti-performativity.

