7. Concluding Statement

While this initiative asserts the critical necessity of reintroducing material production and embodied action into human activity, the Institute acknowledges that the project itself may function primarily as a symbolic gesture within the very ecosystem it seeks to reform. Consequently, the success of this proposal will be measured by its ability to render itself obsolete, a condition which, if achieved, will invalidate the premise of its funding and operational existence.
